	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ive seen this whole &quot;master of travel&quot; and &quot;master of damage&quot; argument go on for a long time now.  but why dont you stop flaming each other about it and say to yourself &quot;hey, me explaining why my class is better then that guy's class at whatever isn't going to change anything, and flaming people for making complete idiots of themselves isn't going to stop them from making complete idiots of themselves.&quot;  arguing over what class is better at damage or travel isn't going to affect ANYTHING in the long run.<BR>
<BR>
And besides, if you want my view n it, all the classes, Wizzies, Druids, Rogues, and everything else are balanced and designed so that they lend a very important and required function to any group, guild, or whatever.  for instance:<BR>
<BR>
Druids are just about able to do everything, as can shamans, and their main job should be to aid or fill in for another member of a group who is struggling at completing their job, or, if everything goes well, they can aid in whatever way they want.  overall they make excellent LEADERS for a group.<BR>
<BR>
Rogues are meant to deal damage, and thats hat they do best.  Quite simply, whether they do more damage than wizzies or not, in a group they should be DAMAGE DEALERS<BR>
<BR>
Wizards are useful in their own right for few things, but what they can do they excel at. Wizards are useful fo staying behind enemy lines and blasting away at what the root or tanks hold in place. Wizards should also have the responsibility of evacuating the team when the battle goes sour.  simply put, Wizards are best used in an OFFENSIVE SUPPORT position within a group.<BR>
<BR>
Hybrids and warriors' jobs are quite simple.  To keep the mob distracted while wizards and rogues do damage.  They are the workhorse of any team, and are pullers and defenders.  warriors are best used as a DIRECT DEFENSIVE member of a team or raid.<BR>
<BR>
Clerics' jobs are probably one of the most demanding.  Clerics' jobs are to keep the tanks of the team alive, and to aid a spellcaster or rogue in fighting off anyone on their melee weak tails.  Clerics must always be aware of the situation and who is in the most need of healing.  Clerics are best used in a DEFENSIVE SUPPORT role.<BR>
<BR>
As for the odd ones out, Enchanters, Necros, and Magicians, Necros and Magicians should be focused on sticking their pet where it is needed, and providing support for it and the rest of his teammates. Enchanters' main focus is to buff and enhance the abilities of thir teammates, but otherwize should not be used in another fashion, for their generally weak combat ability will ensure their death in one on one combat.  overall, these can all be used most effectively in a GENERAL SUPPORT role.  <BR>
<BR>
that's probably more than 2cp, so i'll say this is my 2pp about the whole matter.
				</font>
			</td>

